# ============================================================
# LIFE CORE POLICY
# ============================================================

status: canonical
layer: policy
domain: life
scope: life.core
system: civilization-os
owner: Boss
prepared_by: Zero

## purpose
Defines policy constraints for life.

## policy_rules
Life policy constrains:
- who may view which life states
- who may mutate which life states
- which transitions require review
- what may be disclosed publicly or privately
- how historical life data must be handled

## required_behavior
- disclosure scope must be explicit
- mutation scope must be explicit
- current/historical handling must be explicit
- denial behavior must be explicit

## disclosure_matrix
- bounded public summary
- actor-scoped detail
- operator/reviewer detail
- historical reference detail
- denied output

## allowed_denied_matrix
- allow bounded read only for valid scope
- allow mutation only for valid authority and transition basis
- allow historical reference only in valid mode
- deny hidden current/historical merge
- deny disclosure beyond allowed scope

## escalation_rules
If continuity basis,
transition basis,
authority,
or disclosure scope is unclear,
the path must stop and escalate.

## review_checklist
- life disclosure policy is explicit
- mutation policy is explicit
- denial behavior is explicit
- escalation rules are explicit
